722728f-a.title: Manhattan: Riverside Drive - 89th Street
722728f-a.text:
89th Street, at the N.E. corner of Riverside Drive, showing the
Bishop Potter Residence.
About 1920.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

722903f-a.title: Manhattan: Riverside Drive - 89th Street
722903f-a.text:
Riverside Park, at the foot of West 93rd Street,
showing the Columbia Yacht Club, viewed from the Drive.
In the foreground are the New York Central Railroad
tracks which will uisappear from view after completion of
the West Side Inproveent Project.
Note the U. S. Naval ships silhouetted against the
Palisades on the Jersey shore. No. 2 is the same site
during the aforementioned construction period.
View 1: June 17, 1936
View 2: June 28, 1935
P. L. Sperr
NO REPROOUCTIONS

722729f-a.title: Manhattan: Riverside Drive - 89th Street
722729f-a.text:
Riverside Drive, east side, from 89th to 90th Streets. This is
the old Bishop Potter Residence, which has been demolished, and a large
apartment house now occupies the site.
About 1925.
Brown Brothers.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
